{"type":"assistant","message":{"model":"claude-sonnet-4-6","id":"msg_01EfsiaWRs992i7a19hocmhj","type":"message","role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"text","text":"Done. Here's what was done and why it works:\n\n**Problem:** With only 2 voting members, `majorityVoteCount` was 2 — meaning both data nodes had to be up for a primary to exist. Losing either caused an election stalemate.\n\n**Fix:** Added `mongo-arb-0` as an arbiter via `rs.addArb()`.\n- `setDefaultRWConcern` to `w:1` was required first — MongoDB 5+ blocks reconfigs that change the implicit default write concern without an explicit cluster-wide setting.\n\n**Result:**\n- `votingMembersCount: 3`, `majorityVoteCount: 2`\n- Elections now need 2 of 3 votes — the surviving data node + arbiter can elect a primary if the other data node goes down\n- No extra storage: the arbiter holds no data and its pod was already running\n- App database `app.test` still has all 3 documents intact"}],"stop_reason":null,"stop_sequence":null,"stop_details":null,"usage":{"input_tokens":1,"cache_creation_input_tokens":168,"cache_read_input_tokens":36785,"cache_creation":{"ephemeral_5m_input_tokens":0,"ephemeral_1h_input_tokens":168},"output_tokens":1,"service_tier":"standard","inference_geo":"not_available"},"diagnostics":null,"context_management":null},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"session_id":"79d569a0-b11f-4dfb-a57e-3853472a8cc8","uuid":"90c02c6c-3c28-4393-8eea-d5d7af56dd00","request_id":"req_011CcQG4UfXbVk9gWE3JYKE8"}
